<h2> Session #2: </h2>
<p> The players head back to the village to a warm welcome having rescued little Timmy. Upon returning they are informed that a secret relic, a bone of a saint, of the local godess Thamal (Θαμάλ) -a local diety of fertility and agriculture- has been stolen. Moreover the players still don't know what became of the wizard. Looking for clues they discover that the wizard had visited a local brothel and not before their arrival fled to a nearby farm. On the farm they find an amulet (see picture below).

<p> Unsure how to proceed the players ask around Greenhill (Πρασινόλοφος), Tower (Πύργος) and Cherrytree (Κερασιά) about the amulet, to no avail. However they learn of mysterious fellow by the name of Thadeus, belonging to a strange humanoid rat race, that has psychic abilites, who may be able to help them. After finding Thadeus he agrees to help, under the condition that the players settle his debt to a local gang.</p>

<p>The players manage to settle the debt by agreeing to collect somebody else's debt to the gang. After they collect the debt and return the money to the gang, Thaddeus reveals to them that the amulet belongs to a member of an evil cabal of wizards, known as the wizards of Baldom, that worship the twin gods of dark magic, Molag and Bal, who created the ratfolk as an experimental slave race. With the help of Thaddeus' psychic abilites, they manage to track down the wizard and capture him. However the wizard touches the amulet at the last minute and uses it to teleport him and the party to the ruinous ancient city of Baldom.</p> 
